on affirms the unparalleled diversity of choreographic methods in American dance, and also suggests a critical perspective from which to reflect on dance making and viewing.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aDance. 4aGeneral. 4aPerforming Arts. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / General.2bisacsh1 aLeigh Foster, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052006333440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052090880240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520908802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520908802/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles